{"title_page": "Donagh Maher", "text_new": "{{Infobox GAA player\n| code= Hurling\n| sport = Hurling\n| image = \n| name = Donagh Maher \n| irish = Donagh \u00d3 Meachair\n| fullname = \n| feet = 5\n| inches = 10 \n| occupation = Account manager\n| county = Tipperary\n| province = Munster\n| club = [[Burgess GAA|Burgess]]\n| cposition =\n| clubs = \n| clyears = 2005\u2013present\n| clapps(points) = \n| clcounty = 0\n| clprovince= \n| clallireland =\n| colleges = [[Galway-Mayo Institute of Technology]]\n| colyears = 2007-2012\n| fitz = 0\n| counties = [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n| icposition = Right corner-back\n| icyears = 2012\u20132019\n| icapps(points) = \n| icprovince = 2\n| icallireland = 2\n| nhl = 0\n| allstars = 0\n| clupdate = \n| icupdate = 22:56, 6 August 2019\n| birth_date={{Birth date and age|1988|7|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place=[[Burgess, County Tipperary|Burgess]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n''' Donagh Maher''' (born 28 July 1988) is an Irish [[hurling|hurler]] who plays for [[Tipperary Senior Hurling Championship|Tipperary Senior Championship]] club [[Burgess GAA|Burgess]] and previously at inter-county level for the [[Tipperary senior hurling team]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/premier-making-the-right-moves-195441.html|title=Premier making the right moves |date= 28 May 2012|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=29 May 2012 }}</ref> \n\nOn 22 October 2019, Maher announced his retirement from inter-county hurling.<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.the42.ie/donagh-maher-retires-from-tipperary-4863100-Oct2019/|title ='A huge privilege' - Two-time All-Ireland winner announces Tipperary retirement|date=22 October 2019|work=The 42|accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2019/1023/1085056-tipp-defender-donagh-maher-announces-his-retirement/|title =Tipperary All-Ireland winner Donagh Maher announces retirement|date=22 October 2019|work=RTE Sport|accessdate=23 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Team\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! colspan=\"3\" |[[National Hurling League|National League]]\n! colspan=\"2\" |[[Munster Senior Hurling Championship|Munster]]\n! colspan=\"2\" |[[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|All-Ireland]]\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Score\n!Apps\n!Score\n!Apps\n!Score\n!Apps\n!Score\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" |[[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|2012\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[National Hurling League|Division 1A]]\n|5\n|0-0\n|3\n|0-0\n|2\n|0-0\n|10\n|0-0\n|-\n|2013\n|4\n|0-0\n|0\n|0-00\n|0\n|0-00\n|4\n|0-0\n|-\n|2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n|-\n|2015\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014\n|-\n|2016\n|0\n|0-00\n|2\n|0-0\n|1\n|0-0\n|3\n|0-0\n|-\n|2017\n|3\n|0-00\n|0\n|0-00\n|4\n|0-0\n|7\n|0-00\n|-\n|2018\n|5\n|0-01\n|2\n|0-00\n| colspan=\"2\" |0         0-00\n|7\n|0-00\n|-\n|2019\n|4\n|0-00\n|0\n|0-00\n|0\n|0-00\n|4\n|0-00\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Career total\n!21\n!0-01\n!7\n!0-00\n!7\n!0-0\n!35\n!0-1\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n;Tipperary\n*[[All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship]] (2): [[2016 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2016]], [[2019 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2019]]\n*[[Munster Senior Hurling Championship]] (2): [[2012 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship#Munster Senior Hurling Championship|2012]], [[2016 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship#Munster Senior Hurling Championship|2016]]\n*[[Waterford Crystal Cup]] (1): 2012\n*[[All-Ireland Minor Hurling Championship]] (1): [[2006 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship|2006]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n*[https://tipperary.gaa.ie/players/donagh-maher/ Donagh Maher profile] at the Tipperary GAA website\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Donagh Maher navigation boxes\n|bg=\n|fg=\n|list1=\n{{Tipperary Hurling Team 2016}}\n{{Tipperary Hurling Team 2019}}\n}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maher, Donagh}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Burgess hurlers]]\n[[Category:Tipperary inter-county hurlers]]\n[[Category:Hurling backs]]\n[[Category:All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship winners]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Galway-Mayo Institute of Technology]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox GAA player\n| code= Hurling\n| sport = Hurling\n| image = \n| name = Donagh Maher \n| irish = Donagh \u00d3 Meachair\n| fullname = \n| feet = 5\n| inches = 10 \n| occupation = Account manager\n| county = Tipperary\n| province = Munster\n| club = [[Burgess GAA|Burgess]]\n| cposition =\n| clubs = \n| clyears = 2005\u2013present\n| clapps(points) = \n| clcounty = 0\n| clprovince= \n| clallireland =\n| colleges = [[Galway-Mayo Institute of Technology]]\n| colyears = 2007-2012\n| fitz = 0\n| counties = [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n| icposition = Right corner-back\n| icyears = 2012\u20132019\n| icapps(points) = \n| icprovince = 2\n| icallireland = 2\n| nhl = 0\n| allstars = 0\n| clupdate = \n| icupdate = 22:56, 6 August 2019\n| birth_date={{Birth date and age|1988|7|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place=[[Burgess, County Tipperary|Burgess]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n''' Donagh Maher''' (born 28 July 1988) is an Irish [[hurling|hurler]] who plays for [[Tipperary Senior Hurling Championship|Tipperary Senior Championship]] club [[Burgess GAA|Burgess]] and previously at inter-county level for the [[Tipperary senior hurling team]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/premier-making-the-right-moves-195441.html|title=Premier making the right moves |date= 28 May 2012|publisher=Irish Examiner|accessdate=29 May 2012 }}</ref> \n\nOn 22 October 2019, Maher announced his retirement from inter-county hurling.<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.the42.ie/donagh-maher-retires-from-tipperary-4863100-Oct2019/|title ='A huge privilege' - Two-time All-Ireland winner announces Tipperary retirement|