99-2014) <br><small>MP for [[Glasgow Govan (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Govan]] (1973-1974)</small>\n|2 June 1974<ref name=\":4\" />\n|15 September 1979<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Douglas Henderson (SNP politician)|Douglas Henderson]] <br><small>(1935-2006)</small> <br><small>(2nd Term)</small>\n|[[File:Male portrait placeholder cropped.jpg|128x128px]]\n|MP for [[East Aberdeenshire (UK Parliament constituency)|East Aberdeenshire]] (1974-1979) \n|15 September 1979<ref name=\":5\" />\n|30 May 1981<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Jim Fairlie]]<br><small>(b. 1940)</small>\n|[[File:Male portrait placeholder cropped.jpg|128x128px]]\n|''<small>Candidate for [[Dunfermline West (UK Parliament constituency)|Dunfermline West]] ([[1983 United Kingdom general election|1983]])</small>''\n|30 May 1981<ref name=\":6\" />\n|15 September 1984<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Margaret Ewing]] <br><small>(1945-2006)</small>\n|[[File:Male portrait placeholder cropped.jpg|128x128px]]\n|MSP for [[Moray (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Moray]] (1999-2006) <br><small>MP for [[Moray (UK Parliament constituency)|Moray]] (1987-2001)</small> <br><small>MP for [[East Dunbartonshire (UK Parliament constituency)|East Dunbartonshire]] (1974-1979)</small>\n|15 September 1984<ref name=\":7\" />\n|26 September 1987<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://aberdeensnp.org/node/9|title=HISTORY OF THE SNP {{!}} Aberdeen SNP|website=aberdeensnp.org|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|<small>[[The Right Honourable|The Right Hon.]]</small> [[Alex Salmond]] <br><small>(b. 1954)</small>\n|[[Fi